# ☁️ SNS + ALARMES

## Criar tópico SNS

```bash
SNS=$(aws sns create-topic --name lab-alertas --query TopicArn --output text)

aws sns subscribe --topic-arn $SNS --protocol email \
--notification-endpoint SEU@EMAIL.COM
```

⚠️ Confirmar o email recebido.

---

# PEGAR ID DA EC2

```bash
ID=$(aws ec2 describe-instances \
--filters 'Name=tag:Name,Values=lab-monitoring' \
--query 'Reservations[0].Instances[0].InstanceId' \
--output text)
```

---

# ALARME CPU

```bash
aws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm --alarm-name 'Lab-CPU' \
--metric-name CPUUtilization \
--namespace AWS/EC2 \
--statistic Average \
--period 300 \
--threshold 70 \
--comparison-operator GreaterThanThreshold \
--evaluation-periods 2 \
--dimensions Name=InstanceId,Value=$ID \
--alarm-actions $SNS \
--ok-actions $SNS
```

---

# TESTAR ALARME

```bash
aws cloudwatch set-alarm-state --alarm-name 'Lab-CPU' \
--state-value ALARM \
--state-reason 'Teste manual'
```

